subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen.
Tenth tergite with posterior edge straight, unmodified (
Fig. 43E
). Epiproct unmodified; paraprocts unmodified. Cercus long and slender, narrowed towards apex, bent inwards; straight when seen from side; apex truncated, with minute spines (
Fig. 43E, F
). Phallus entirely membranous, without sclerotized elements. Subgenital plate broadly trapezoidal, with narrow incision apically; styli absent (
Fig. 43F
).
